# waQup Design System — Enforcement Rules

## Single Source of Truth

All design tokens live in ONE place:

```
packages/shared/src/theme/tokens.ts   ← canonical numeric values (shared)
packages/web/src/theme/format.ts      ← CSS string adapters (web only)
packages/web/src/theme/index.ts       ← barrel export
```

**Never define a token anywhere else. Never duplicate a token.**

---

## Token Import Pattern

```typescript
// ✅ Always import from @/theme in packages/web
import { spacing, borderRadius, BLUR, colors, HEADER_PADDING_X, NAV_HEIGHT } from '@/theme';

// ❌ Never import design values from anywhere else
import { spacing } from '../../../theme/format';        // wrong path
import { spacing } from '@waqup/shared/theme';          // wrong in web
```

---

## Colors — Never Hardcode

```typescript
// ✅ Use theme colors object
const { theme } = useTheme();
const colors = theme.colors;
style={{ color: colors.text.primary }}
style={{ background: colors.accent.tertiary }}
style={{ border: `1px solid ${colors.glass.border}` }}

// ❌ Never hardcode brand colors
style={{ color: '#A855F7' }}
style={{ background: '#9333EA' }}
style={{ color: 'rgba(168, 85, 247, 0.3)' }}
```

---

## Blur / Backdrop Filter — Always Use BLUR Token

```typescript
// ✅ Use BLUR tokens (SSOT for backdrop-filter values)
import { BLUR } from '@/theme';
backdropFilter: BLUR.lg       // blur(12px) — nav, drawers, footer
backdropFilter: BLUR.xl       // blur(20px) — modals, glass cards
backdropFilter: BLUR.md       // blur(10px) — subtle surfaces
backdropFilter: BLUR.sm       // blur(8px)  — very subtle

// ❌ Never hardcode blur values
backdropFilter: 'blur(12px)'
backdropFilter: 'blur(20px)'
```

Always set BOTH `backdropFilter` and `WebkitBackdropFilter` to the same `BLUR.*` value.

---

## Spacing — Always Use spacing Token

```typescript
// ✅ Use spacing tokens
import { spacing } from '@/theme';
gap: spacing.md           // 16px
padding: spacing.xl       // 32px
marginBottom: spacing.lg  // 24px

// ❌ Never hardcode spacing
gap: '16px'
padding: 32
marginBottom: '24px'
```

---

## Nav / Header Padding — Always Use HEADER_PADDING_X

```typescript
// ✅ Correct — consistent with the header token (80px)
import { HEADER_PADDING_X } from '@/theme';
paddingLeft: HEADER_PADDING_X
paddingRight: HEADER_PADDING_X

// ❌ Wrong — breaks visual alignment
paddingLeft: spacing.xl    // too small
paddingLeft: '48px'        // hardcoded
```

---

## Token Lifecycle

### Adding a New Token
1. Add the canonical numeric value to `packages/shared/src/theme/tokens.ts`
2. Add the CSS string export to `packages/web/src/theme/format.ts`
3. Add to the barrel export in `packages/web/src/theme/index.ts`
4. Use it immediately — never add a token without a real usage

### Removing a Token
1. Verify zero usages with a project-wide search before removing
2. Remove from `tokens.ts`, `format.ts`, and `index.ts` in one commit
3. Dead exports are technical debt — remove them immediately when discovered

---

## Do NOT Use the `waqup-app/` Directory

The root-level `waqup-app/` folder is the **old monolithic app** — deprecated, not part of the monorepo. Do not edit or reference any files under `waqup-app/`.

**Active codebase:**
- `packages/web/` — Next.js web app
- `packages/mobile/` — React Native / Expo mobile app
- `packages/shared/` — Shared business logic, tokens, types

---

## Redundancy Checklist (Before Committing)

- [ ] No new hardcoded hex colors added
- [ ] No new hardcoded `blur(Xpx)` values — use `BLUR.*`
- [ ] No new hardcoded spacing values — use `spacing.*`
- [ ] No dead token exports left in `format.ts` / `index.ts`
- [ ] New tokens are added to `tokens.ts` first, then `format.ts`, then `index.ts`
- [ ] All three token files updated atomically (never partially)
